******
[1] Azerbaijan, suspected
Date: Thu 22 Aug 2013
Source: Salam News Agency, Azerbaijan [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.salamnews.org/ru/news/read/89543/pv-azerbaydane-chislo-rayonov-gde-obnarujen-virus-%D0%91%D0%B0%D0%BA%D1%83


In Azerbaijan, the number of areas in which Schmallenberg virus [SBV] has been found in cattle reached 26, in 9 regions. This has been told to Salam News by the Head of the State Veterinary Service, Sial Rustamov.

According to her, since yesterday [21 Aug 2013] when the virus was found in 17 districts, the number has now risen to 26.

"This virus is spreading rapidly. Initially, it was detected in the areas of Aran-Imishli, Neftchala, Salyan, Sabirabad, Kurdamir, Beylagan and others, but now its presence has been revealed in animals in Ismayilli, Gabala, Agsu, Astara, Khojavend and Gobustan. Overall, around 22-25 percent of the cattle in 26 areas are infected with this transmissible virus."

--
